## 🏗️ 3. System Architecture

FUGEN SmartPay follows a **three-tier client-server architecture** consisting of:

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Frontend Clients"
        A["🖥️ Admin Dashboard<br>(React + Vite + Electron)"]
        B["📱 Mobile POS App<br>(React Native + Expo)"]
        C["🎓 Student Portal<br>(React Web)"]
    end

    subgraph "Backend Server"
        D["🔧 Node.js + Express API<br>(Port 5000)"]
        E["🔌 Socket.IO Server<br>(Real-Time Events)"]
    end

    subgraph "Cloud Database"
        F["🔥 Google Firebase<br>Cloud Firestore"]
    end

    A <-->|HTTP + WebSocket| D
    B <-->|HTTP + WebSocket| D
    C <-->|HTTP + WebSocket| D
    D <--> E
    D <-->|Firebase Admin SDK| F
```

### Key Architectural Decisions

1. **Firebase Admin SDK Only** — All clients communicate through the Node.js backend API. **No client directly accesses Firestore**, ensuring all data operations are controlled and validated server-side. Firestore security rules deny all direct client access (`allow read, write: if false`).
2. **Socket.IO for Real-Time** — Every mutation (purchase, top-up, student creation/deletion) emits a Socket.IO event, causing all connected clients to refresh their data automatically.
3. **Electron for Desktop** — The Admin Dashboard can run as a native desktop application via Electron, or as a standard web app in the browser.
4. **Cloud Deployment** — Backend is deployed to **Render.com** (`https://fugen-backend.onrender.com`), frontend is deployable to Replit or any static host.

