## 💰 7. Core Functionalities

### 7.1 Student Management

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| **Create Student** | Register with Full Name, Grade/Section, LRN; auto-generates Student ID (`S2026-XXXXXX`) and passkey |
| **View Students** | Table with Student ID, Name, Grade/Section, Balance (color-coded green/red), Actions |
| **Search Students** | Search by name, ID, or grade |
| **Edit Student** | Update name, grade/section, Student ID, LRN, and passkey |
| **Delete Student** | Single or bulk checkbox selection with confirmation dialog |
| **Bulk Import** | CSV file upload to create multiple students at once |
| **Export Data** | Export student list and transaction data as CSV |
| **View QR Code** | Generate and display QR code card for each student |
| **Download/Print QR** | Download QR as image or print directly; bulk PDF download available |

### 7.2 Financial Transactions

| Transaction Type | Location | Description |
|---|---|---|
| **TOPUP** | Admin Dashboard | Add points to a student's balance (cash intake at the office) |
| **PURCHASE** | Canteen POS (Mobile) | Deduct points for a canteen purchase |
| **DEDUCTION** | Admin Dashboard | Manually deduct points (requires Admin PIN) |
| **WITHDRAWAL** | Admin Dashboard | Record cash withdrawal from the system (requires Admin PIN) |
| **CREDIT** | Canteen POS | Automatic when a purchase exceeds the student's balance (up to -500 points limit) |

### 7.3 Credit System
- Students can go into **negative balance** up to a maximum debt of **-500 points**
- Purchases that would exceed the credit limit are **blocked**
- When a student's balance is negative, a **credit warning** is shown before proceeding
- Debts are displayed in **red** across all interfaces
- The system distinguishes between the **cash portion** and **credit portion** of each purchase

### 7.4 Top-Up Request System
- **Students** can submit a reservation request to top-up their balance through the Student Portal
- Requests include: **Amount**, **Preferred Date**, and **Time Slot**
- **Admin** can manage requests with the following actions:
  - ✅ **Approve** — Accepts the reservation and notifies the student
  - ❌ **Reject** — Denies the reservation with a notification
  - 📅 **Reschedule** — Moves the reservation to a new date/time
  - 💰 **Resolve** — Completes the top-up (adds balance, logs transaction, notifies student)
  - ↩️ **Undo** — Reverses a resolved request
- Each action sends an **in-app notification** to the student

### 7.5 Notification System
- Students receive notifications in their portal for:
  - Reservation accepted / rejected / rescheduled
  - Top-up completed
- Notifications can be marked as read
- Fetched via `GET /api/student/:studentId/notifications`

### 7.6 Cash Management
- **Cash on Hand**: Calculated from total top-ups minus withdrawals
- **Manual Cash Adjustment**: Admin can set a manual override for the cash-on-hand display (requires Admin PIN)
- **System Debt**: Sum of all negative student balances (outstanding credit)

### 7.7 Reporting & Statistics

| Report | Description |
|---|---|
| **Daily Stats** | Total sales (canteen), cash collected vs. credit, top-ups, withdrawals for a given day |
| **Weekly Stats** | 7-day bar chart of canteen purchase totals |
| **Historical Reports** | Browse saved daily reports by month and day |
| **Monthly Export** | Export monthly reports as CSV |
| **Audit Log** | Local log of admin actions (stored in browser `localStorage`) |

### 7.8 Daily Report Auto-Save
- The mobile app runs a **DailyReportService** that automatically saves a snapshot of daily statistics to `AsyncStorage` at **3:30 PM** every day
- Reports can be browsed in the **Reports** screen on the mobile app
- Each report captures: canteen sales, cash collected, credit sales, system top-ups, withdrawals, cash-on-hand, and outstanding credit

