## 📡 8. API Endpoints

### Student Routes

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `POST` | `/api/student` | Create a new student |
| `GET` | `/api/students` | Get all students |
| `GET` | `/api/student/:studentId` | Get a specific student |
| `PUT` | `/api/student/:studentId` | Update student info |
| `DELETE` | `/api/student/:studentId` | Delete a student |
| `POST` | `/api/verify-passkey` | Verify student passkey (login) |
| `POST` | `/api/student/update-passkey` | Change student passkey |
| `GET` | `/api/student/:studentId/notifications` | Get student notifications |
| `PUT` | `/api/notifications/:id/read` | Mark notification as read |

### Transaction Routes

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `POST` | `/api/topup` | Add balance to a student |
| `POST` | `/api/deduct` | Remove balance (admin only) |
| `POST` | `/api/purchase` | Process a canteen purchase |
| `POST` | `/api/withdraw` | Record a cash withdrawal |
| `GET` | `/api/transactions` | Get transaction history (optional `?studentId=`) |
| `GET` | `/api/stats/daily` | Get daily statistics (optional `?date=&location=`) |
| `GET` | `/api/stats/weekly` | Get 7-day sales chart data |
| `POST` | `/api/cash-adjustment` | Set manual cash-on-hand override |
| `GET` | `/api/cash-adjustment` | Get current cash adjustment |

### Top-Up Request Routes

| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `POST` | `/api/request-topup` | Submit a top-up reservation request |
| `GET` | `/api/topup-requests` | Get all pending/accepted requests |
| `PUT` | `/api/topup-requests/:id/approve` | Approve a request |
| `PUT` | `/api/topup-requests/:id/reject` | Reject a request |
| `PUT` | `/api/topup-requests/:id/reschedule` | Reschedule a request |
| `PUT` | `/api/topup-requests/:id/resolve` | Complete the top-up |
| `PUT` | `/api/topup-requests/:id/undo` | Undo a resolved request |

---

## 🔌 9. Real-Time Synchronization (Socket.IO)

All platforms connect to the same Socket.IO server for live data synchronization.

| Event Name | Trigger | Effect |
|---|---|---|
| `balanceUpdate` | After any top-up, purchase, deduction, withdrawal, or notification | All connected clients refresh their data (stats, balances, transactions) |
| `studentCreated` | After a new student is registered | Student lists refresh across all clients |
| `studentDeleted` | After a student is removed | Student lists refresh across all clients |

---

## 🖥️ 10. Platform Descriptions

### 10.1 Web Admin Dashboard (Desktop / Browser)

The **primary management interface** for school administrators. Built with React, Vite, and Ant Design.

**Access Flow**: Intro/About Page → Select Portal (Admin or Student) → Login → Dashboard

**Admin Dashboard Features** (Sidebar Navigation):
1. **Users Tab** — Student management table with search, add/edit/delete, QR code generation, bulk import/export
2. **Canteen Tab** — Live canteen transaction feed with daily stats (total sales, points scanned, credits)
3. **Reports Tab** — Historical daily report browser with weekly sales chart, monthly CSV export
4. **Top-Up Requests Tab** — Manage student reservation requests (approve/reject/reschedule/resolve)
5. **System Tab** — Cash-on-hand display (with manual override), total system debt, creditor list, withdrawal functionality
6. **Audit Log** — View admin action history

**Student Dashboard Features** (accessible via Student Portal login):
1. **Balance Display** — Current points balance with color-coded positive/negative
2. **QR Code** — Personal QR code for canteen scanning
3. **Transaction History** — View past top-ups, purchases, and deductions
4. **Top-Up Request** — Submit a reservation to top-up balance
5. **Notifications** — In-app notification inbox
6. **Change Passkey** — Update personal 4-digit passkey
7. **Spending Chart** — Visual history of transactions

### 10.2 Mobile POS App (Canteen Terminal)

The **canteen point-of-sale terminal** used by canteen staff to process student purchases. Built with React Native and Expo.

**Screen Flow**: Login → Home → Scan QR → Identify Student → Passkey Verification (optional) → Purchase Entry → Confirmation

**Mobile Screens**:
1. **LoginScreen** — Admin credentials login with "Keep me Signed In" option
2. **HomeScreen** — Main dashboard with large SCAN button, plus quick access to System, Requests, Users, and Reports
3. **ScanScreen** — Live camera QR scanner with daily sales stats footer; identifies `FUGEN:` prefixed QR codes; haptic vibration on scan
4. **PasskeyScreen** — 4-digit passkey verification (or bypass option)
5. **PurchaseScreen** — Transaction entry with student info, balance display, amount input, quick preset buttons (5, 10, 15, 20), credit limit enforcement, and success sound effect
6. **SystemDataScreen** — System overview (cash-on-hand, total debt)
7. **TransactionHistoryScreen** — Browse all student users
8. **ReportsScreen** — Browse auto-saved daily reports
9. **DayDetailsScreen** — Drill-down into a specific day's report
10. **TopupRequestsScreen** — View and manage top-up requests from mobile

