## 🔄 11. Data Flow Diagrams

### 11.1 Student Registration Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor Admin
    participant Web as Admin Dashboard
    participant API as Backend API
    participant DB as Firestore
    participant WS as Socket.IO

    Admin->>Web: Fill form (Name, Grade, LRN)
    Web->>Web: Auto-generate passkey from LRN
    Web->>API: POST /api/student
    API->>API: Generate Student ID (S2026-XXXXXX)
    API->>API: Hash passkey with bcrypt
    API->>DB: Store student document
    API->>WS: Emit 'studentCreated'
    WS-->>Web: Refresh student list
    API-->>Web: Return Student ID + QR data
    Web->>Admin: Display success modal with credentials
```

### 11.2 Canteen Purchase Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor Staff as Canteen Staff
    participant App as Mobile POS
    participant API as Backend API
    participant DB as Firestore
    participant WS as Socket.IO
    participant Web as Admin Dashboard

    Staff->>App: Scan Student QR Code
    App->>App: Parse FUGEN:StudentID
    App->>Staff: Show "Student Identified" modal
    Staff->>App: Choose Proceed or Require Passkey
    
    alt Require Passkey
        App->>API: POST /api/verify-passkey
        API->>DB: Verify bcrypt hash
        API-->>App: Verified
    end
    
    Staff->>App: Enter purchase amount
    App->>API: POST /api/purchase
    API->>DB: Firestore Transaction (atomic)
    Note over API,DB: Deduct balance, log transaction
    API->>WS: Emit 'balanceUpdate'
    WS-->>Web: Dashboard refreshes stats
    WS-->>App: POS refreshes daily stats
    API-->>App: Success
    App->>App: Play success sound 🔊
    App->>App: Navigate back to Scan screen
```

### 11.3 Top-Up Request Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor Student
    participant Portal as Student Portal
    participant API as Backend API
    participant DB as Firestore
    participant WS as Socket.IO
    participant Admin as Admin Dashboard

    Student->>Portal: Submit top-up request (amount, date, time)
    Portal->>API: POST /api/request-topup
    API->>DB: Store in topUpRequests collection
    API-->>Portal: Request confirmed

    Admin->>Admin: View pending requests
    Admin->>API: PUT /api/topup-requests/:id/approve
    API->>DB: Update status to ACCEPTED
    API->>DB: Create notification for student
    API->>WS: Emit 'balanceUpdate'
    WS-->>Portal: Student sees notification

    Note over Admin: Student visits office with cash
    Admin->>API: PUT /api/topup-requests/:id/resolve
    API->>DB: Add balance, log transaction
    API->>DB: Update status to RESOLVED
    API->>DB: Create "Top-Up Completed" notification
    API->>WS: Emit 'balanceUpdate'
    WS-->>Portal: Balance updates in real-time
```

