## 🛠️ 12. Step-by-Step Development Process

### Phase 1: Planning & Design
1. Analyzed the canteen payment problem at FGPIS (long queues, cash handling errors, no transaction tracking)
2. Designed a cashless solution using QR codes on student IDs
3. Selected technology stack: React (web), React Native (mobile), Node.js (backend), Firebase (database)
4. Designed the database schema with Firestore collections: `students`, `transactions`, `topUpRequests`, `notifications`, `systemSettings`

### Phase 2: Backend Development
1. Initialized Node.js + Express project with Firebase Admin SDK
2. Created [firebase.js](file:///c:/Users/melma/OneDrive/Desktop/CAPSTONE-2/backend/src/config/firebase.js) config with support for local file and environment variable credentials
3. Built [studentController.js](file:///c:/Users/melma/OneDrive/Desktop/CAPSTONE-2/backend/src/controllers/studentController.js) with CRUD operations:
   - Student creation with auto-generated IDs and bcrypt-hashed passkeys
   - Passkey verification with failed attempt tracking and account lockout
   - LRN-based passkey generation algorithm
4. Built [transactionController.js](file:///c:/Users/melma/OneDrive/Desktop/CAPSTONE-2/backend/src/controllers/transactionController.js) with financial operations:
   - Top-up, Purchase, Deduction, and Withdrawal handlers using Firestore transactions (atomic operations)
   - Daily and weekly statistics aggregation
   - Credit/cash split calculation for purchases
5. Implemented Socket.IO for real-time event broadcasting
6. Defined RESTful API routes in [apiRoutes.js](file:///c:/Users/melma/OneDrive/Desktop/CAPSTONE-2/backend/src/routes/apiRoutes.js)
7. Added security middleware (Helmet, CORS)
8. Configured the server to serve the frontend build as static files for cloud deployment

### Phase 3: Admin Dashboard (Frontend)
1. Initialized React project with Vite
2. Installed Ant Design for UI components and Recharts for data visualization
3. Built [LoginPage.jsx](file:///c:/Users/melma/OneDrive/Desktop/CAPSTONE-2/frontend/src/pages/LoginPage.jsx) with multi-role authentication:
   - Intro/About page with project overview and team credits
   - Portal selection (Admin vs Student)
   - Admin login form and Student login/registration forms
4. Built [NewAdminDashboard.jsx](file:///c:/Users/melma/OneDrive/Desktop/CAPSTONE-2/frontend/src/pages/NewAdminDashboard.jsx) (1,400+ lines) as the main admin interface:
   - Sidebar navigation with Users, Canteen, Reports, Requests, System tabs
   - Student management table with search, filters, checkbox selection
   - QR code generation and composite card builder (QR + student info)
   - Bulk import (CSV), bulk PDF export, and data export functionality
   - Real-time transaction feed with daily statistics
   - Weekly sales bar chart
   - Top-up request management with approve/reject/reschedule/resolve actions
   - System cash management with manual override capability
   - Audit log tracking
5. Built [StudentDashboard.jsx](file:///c:/Users/melma/OneDrive/Desktop/CAPSTONE-2/frontend/src/pages/StudentDashboard.jsx) as the student self-service portal:
   - Balance display, QR code viewer, transaction history
   - Top-up request submission with date/time selection
   - Notifications inbox with real-time updates
   - Passkey change functionality
   - Spending chart visualization
6. Set up Socket.IO client for real-time data synchronization
7. Configured Electron wrapper for desktop application distribution

### Phase 4: Mobile POS App
1. Initialized React Native project with Expo
2. Set up React Navigation (Stack Navigator) for screen navigation
3. Built [LoginScreen.js](file:///c:/Users/melma/OneDrive/Desktop/CAPSTONE-2/mobile-app/src/screens/LoginScreen.js) with credential authentication and AsyncStorage persistence
4. Built [HomeScreen.js](file:///c:/Users/melma/OneDrive/Desktop/CAPSTONE-2/mobile-app/src/screens/HomeScreen.js) as the main navigation hub with a large Scan button
5. Built [ScanScreen.js](file:///c:/Users/melma/OneDrive/Desktop/CAPSTONE-2/mobile-app/src/screens/ScanScreen.js) with Expo Camera QR scanner:
   - Barcode scanning with validation (`FUGEN:` prefix check)
   - "Student Identified" modal with passkey bypass option
   - Live daily statistics footer
   - Haptic feedback on successful scan
6. Built [PasskeyScreen.js](file:///c:/Users/melma/OneDrive/Desktop/CAPSTONE-2/mobile-app/src/screens/PasskeyScreen.js) for student identity verification
7. Built [PurchaseScreen.js](file:///c:/Users/melma/OneDrive/Desktop/CAPSTONE-2/mobile-app/src/screens/PurchaseScreen.js) for POS transaction entry:
   - Quick amount buttons (5, 10, 15, 20 points)
   - Credit limit enforcement with confirmation dialogs
   - Success sound effect on completed purchase
8. Built supporting screens: SystemData, TransactionHistory, Reports, DayDetails, TopupRequests
9. Implemented [dailyReportService.js](file:///c:/Users/melma/OneDrive/Desktop/CAPSTONE-2/mobile-app/src/services/dailyReportService.js) for automated daily report saving at 3:30 PM

### Phase 5: Integration & Real-Time
1. Connected all three platforms (web admin, student portal, mobile POS) to the same backend
2. Implemented Socket.IO event handling across all clients:
   - `balanceUpdate` → refresh stats and balances
   - `studentCreated` / `studentDeleted` → refresh student lists
3. Verified cross-platform synchronization: a purchase on the mobile POS instantly reflects on the admin dashboard and student portal

### Phase 6: Cloud Deployment
1. Deployed backend to **Render.com** as a Node.js web service
2. Configured Firebase credentials via **Base64-encoded environment variable** (`FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_BASE64`) for secure cloud deployment
3. Built frontend production bundle with Vite and configured the backend to serve it as static files
4. Updated all API base URLs in frontend and mobile app to point to the Render deployment
5. Prepared **Replit** deployment guide as an alternative hosting option

### Phase 7: Polish & Refinement
1. Updated currency labels from "SAR" to "Points/Pts" across all interfaces
2. Implemented session persistence (localStorage on web, AsyncStorage on mobile)
3. Added manual cash adjustment override for the System tab
4. Enhanced QR code recognition format (`FUGEN:StudentID`) for reliable scanning
5. Optimized Firestore queries to prevent quota exhaustion (removed full-table scans)
6. Added credit transaction categorization (PURCHASE vs CREDIT distinction)
7. Themed the mobile scanner "Student Identified" alert to match the app's dark blue and purple color scheme
8. Implemented the student top-up request/reservation workflow with notification system

